components.name: Create Analytics Table via CTAS
components.description: Executes a Snowflake CTAS query to build an analytics table from raw data, validates that the temporary table contains rows, and atomically swaps it into the production schema.
inputs: table_params (dictionary with schema, table name, and SQL query)

upstream_policy.description: Runs after the previous tablecreation task completes successfully, preserving the strict linear order.

connections.purpose: Execute CTAS and ALTER TABLE SWAP statements in Snowflake

components.name: Slack Failure Notifier
components.description: Sends a Slack alert when a pipeline task fails, using the configured onfailure callback.
outputs: Slack message posted to configured channel

upstream_policy.description: Triggered when any upstream task fails.

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)
